00:08:29,346 --> 00:08:30,972
And I never miss <i>The Today Show.</i>

242
00:08:31,056 --> 00:08:34,017
They have a monkey… J. Fred Muggs.

243
00:08:34,101 --> 00:08:35,727
He's such a funny monkey.

244
00:08:35,811 --> 00:08:37,020
ROSE: Are those onions?

245
00:08:37,104 --> 00:08:39,814
Onions and chicken skin for my schmaltz.

246
00:08:39,898 --> 00:08:41,607
Do you have to do that now?

247
00:08:41,691 --> 00:08:43,401
I can't make a schmaltz
in my own kitchen?

248
00:08:43,485 --> 00:08:45,028
Is that what you're saying?

249
00:08:45,112 --> 00:08:48,156
It's just a little early
for such a strong smell.

250
00:08:48,240 --> 00:08:50,783
Why is the TV on when the radio is on?!

251
00:08:50,867 --> 00:08:52,076
Because of the monkey!

252
00:08:52,160 --> 00:08:54,162
-The what?!
-J. Fred Muggs!

253
00:08:54,246 --> 00:08:55,872
-Who!?
-He's a monkey!

254
00:08:55,956 --> 00:08:57,665
Have some bread, Abe!

255
00:08:57,749 --> 00:09:00,626
Zelda burned the first batch,
so I made some for you.

256
00:09:00,710 --> 00:09:02,086
I didn't burn the toast.

257
00:09:02,170 --> 00:09:03,921
I just asked where the toaster was.

258
00:09:04,005 --> 00:09:06,674
I'm going to eat my toast upstairs!

259
00:09:06,758 --> 00:09:08,509
-[UPBEAT TV THEME PLAYS]
-J. Fred Muggs is on!

260
00:09:08,593 --> 00:09:10,345
I'm coming with you, Abe!

261
00:09:10,429 --> 00:09:11,971
SHIRLEY: He's wearing shoes!

262
00:09:12,055 --> 00:09:14,015
Dance, monkey! Dance!

263
00:09:14,099 --> 00:09:15,850
-[SHIRLEY LAUGHS]
-Sh… Should I watch the onions!?

264
00:09:15,934 --> 00:09:17,894
-Mrs. Maisel?
-[SHIRLEY LAUGHS]

265
00:09:17,978 --> 00:09:21,564
[SHIRLEY LAUGHS LOUDLY]

266
00:09:21,648 --> 00:09:24,150
MAN [ON TV]: <i>Dr. Barbara Moore
completes an emphatic demonstration</i>

267
00:09:24,234 --> 00:09:26,484
<i>-about the equality of the sexes…</i>
-[KNOCKING]

268
00:09:26,987 --> 00:09:29,489
Can I be in here with you?

269
00:09:29,573 --> 00:09:31,616
<i>…nuts, honey, milk and natural juices.</i>

270
00:09:31,700 --> 00:09:34,202
<i>The 56-year-old</i>

271
00:09:34,286 --> 00:09:37,997
<i>cheered on by all of Britain completes…</i>

272
00:09:38,081 --> 00:09:41,459
This has been the
longest month of my life.

273
00:09:41,543 --> 00:09:43,962
We've been here a week.

274
00:09:47,716 --> 00:09:51,260
<i>♪ It's a lovely day today ♪</i>

275
00:09:51,344 --> 00:09:53,388
<i>♪ So whatever you've got to do… ♪</i>

276
00:09:53,472 --> 00:09:55,181
A girl could get used to this.

277
00:09:55,265 --> 00:09:56,766
This is really how it works?

278
00:09:56,850 --> 00:09:58,893
Just sits on your face,
like a French whore?

279
00:09:58,977 --> 00:09:59,136
Yup.

280
00:09:59,220 --> 00:10:01,312
Oh.
I look like the Bride of Frankenstein.

281
00:10:01,396 --> 00:10:03,898
Let me even it out it a bit.

282
00:10:03,982 --> 00:10:06,275
This reminds me of those
lazy Bryn Mawr Sundays

283
00:10:06,359 --> 00:10:09,113
when Petra, Janie, Marcie and
I would shake up some cocktails

284
00:10:09,197 --> 00:10:12,157
and dish on boys and treat
ourselves to a beauty regimen.

285
00:10:12,241 --> 00:10:14,576
Mm. Sounds fun. Where's the gang now?

286
00:10:14,660 --> 00:10:17,329
Uh, Janie's a housewife in Pittsburgh,

287
00:10:17,413 --> 00:10:18,914
Marcie teaches high school English,

288
00:10:18,998 --> 00:10:21,208
and Petra raises chickens
in the Hudson Valley.

289
00:10:21,292 --> 00:10:23,502
-You thought I was serious?
-You're all set.

290
00:10:23,586 --> 00:10:26,213
Now sit, relax and let it work its magic.

291
00:10:26,297 --> 00:10:28,424
[SUSIE SIGHS]

292
00:10:28,508 --> 00:10:32,177
<i>♪ But if you've got something
that must be done… ♪</i>

293
00:10:32,261 --> 00:10:33,846
Mine's done. [CLEARS THROAT]

294
00:10:33,930 --> 00:10:35,722
I think I'm cured now,
or beautiful or whatever.

295
00:10:35,806 --> 00:10:37,599
-Do not take that mask off.
-I'm suffocating!

296
00:10:37,683 --> 00:10:39,935
You have to leave it on for half an hour.

297
00:10:40,019 --> 00:10:41,562
Not in a million years!

298
00:10:41,646 --> 00:10:43,939
Fine. Let the desert sun
turn you into an old hag.

299
00:10:44,023 --> 00:10:46,316
I'm a manager.
Nobody cares what the fuck I look like.

300
00:10:46,400 --> 00:10:48,068
[KNOCKING]

301
00:10:48,152 --> 00:10:49,945
Susie, envelope.

302
00:10:50,029 --> 00:10:52,322
The guys said to look
out for the envelope.

303
00:10:52,406 --> 00:10:54,324
Open it. Open it!

304
00:10:54,408 --> 00:10:55,993
Don't rush me. Don't rush me.

305
00:10:56,077 --> 00:10:57,953
I'll get a paper cut.

306
00:10:58,037 --> 00:10:59,371
[SUSIE SIGHS]

307
00:10:59,455 --> 00:11:01,123
Oh, Sweet Jesus, there it is.

308
00:11:01,207 --> 00:11:02,541
Two weeks' pay.

309
00:11:02,625 --> 00:11:04,376
They took taxes out of it.

310
00:11:04,460 --> 00:11:06,462
It's got the casino logo on it. Neat.

311
00:11:06,546 --> 00:11:08,505
Guess I'm gonna have
to start paying taxes.

312
00:11:08,589 --> 00:11:10,632
-We should frame this.
-Then we can't cash it.

313
00:11:10,716 --> 00:11:12,259
Think about it.
When I'm making ten grand a show,

314
00:11:12,343 --> 00:11:13,719
this check won't mean anything,

315
00:11:13,803 --> 00:11:15,095
and it'll be a terrific souvenir.

316
00:11:15,179 --> 00:11:16,680
When you're making ten grand a show,

317
00:11:16,764 --> 00:11:18,765
I'm gonna be so whacked
out on vodka and opium,

318
00:11:18,849 --> 00:11:20,392
nothing's gonna mean anything.

319
00:11:20,476 --> 00:11:22,352
And I'll be there to pull
you out of the gutter.

320
00:11:22,436 --> 00:11:24,354
So, how do we do this?
Put it in your account?

321
00:11:24,438 --> 00:11:26,273
No. No. You take care of the money.

322
00:11:26,357 --> 00:11:27,858
I get money, I spend money.

323
00:11:27,942 --> 00:11:29,568
Then I will do the money.

324
00:11:29,652 --> 00:11:31,403
Hmm. It's a little short.

325
00:11:31,487 --> 00:11:33,238
-Really?
-Not by much.

326
00:11:33,322 --> 00:11:35,324
It's close, but it's definitely short.

327
00:11:35,408 --> 00:11:37,409
-Who do we talk to?
-You don't talk to anybody.

328
00:11:37,493 --> 00:11:39,495
I will talk to Angie before I go.

329
00:11:39,579 --> 00:11:41,371
Go? Go where?

330
00:11:41,455 --> 00:11:44,458
New York. Just for a day or two.
It won't be long.

331
00:11:44,542 --> 00:11:46,168
Sophie stuff?

332
00:11:46,252 --> 00:11:47,794
I said I wouldn't say.

333
00:11:47,878 --> 00:11:49,713
And I said I wouldn't mind, and I don't.

334
00:11:49,797 --> 00:11:51,089
You're kicking ass every night.

335
00:11:51,173 --> 00:11:52,973
And I'll be back before you know it.

336
00:11:53,509 --> 00:11:54,843
Let me hold it while you get ready.

337
00:11:54,927 --> 00:11:58,013
<i>♪ Except it's a lovely day… ♪</i>

338
00:11:58,097 --> 00:11:59,264
Don't get face junk on it.

339
00:11:59,348 --> 00:12:03,685
<i>♪ It's a lovely day. ♪</i>

340
00:12:03,769 --> 00:12:05,771
[TYPEWRITER KEYS CLACKING]

341
00:12:09,775 --> 00:12:11,485
Hi. Is this Angie's office?

342
00:12:11,569 --> 00:12:13,570
-Yep.
-He in?

343
00:12:13,654 --> 00:12:15,197
I represent the showroom comic,

344
00:12:15,281 --> 00:12:16,823
and we have a little
problem with our check.

345
00:12:16,907 --> 00:12:18,075
He's in.

346
00:12:18,159 --> 00:12:19,952
Would, uh, he have time to see me?

347
00:12:20,036 --> 00:12:21,495
Well, he's in with somebody.

348
00:12:21,579 --> 00:12:23,121
He can see you after.

349
00:12:23,205 --> 00:12:24,832
Thanks.

350
00:12:24,916 --> 00:12:28,044
Oh, this arthritis is
really slowing me down.

351
00:12:28,128 --> 00:12:29,671
SUSIE: You're better than me.

352
00:12:29,755 --> 00:12:31,756
Hey, Bobby Darin.

353
00:12:31,840 --> 00:12:33,258
Angie knows Bobby Darin?

354
00:12:33,342 --> 00:12:35,719
Mr. Calibresi knows everybody.

355
00:12:37,804 --> 00:12:39,854
[MAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY IN OTHER ROOM]

356
00:12:42,976 --> 00:12:44,894
MAN: Okay, but let me just explain.

357
00:12:44,978 --> 00:12:46,271
ANGIE: After everything
we've done for you?

358
00:12:46,355 --> 00:12:48,064
For your clients?

359
00:12:48,148 --> 00:12:51,276
-The Stardust of all places?
-[MAN GRUNTS]

360
00:12:51,360 --> 00:12:53,444
Where's your gratitude, Gordy?

361
00:12:53,528 --> 00:12:55,530
-You owe me a little gratitude, I think.
-[BLOW LANDS]

362
00:12:55,614 --> 00:12:57,407
GORDY: Yes, I d… [GRUNTS] Yes, I do.

363
00:12:57,491 --> 00:12:58,700
ANGIE: Vic Damone is mine.

364
00:12:58,784 --> 00:13:01,661
-Yes?
-Yes, Angie, yes.

365
00:13:01,745 --> 00:13:03,079
-[MAN GROANS]
-ANGIE: That's a good answer.

366
00:13:03,163 --> 00:13:04,872
You look like shit.

367
00:13:04,956 --> 00:13:06,708
Clean yourself up and
get the hell out of here.

368
00:13:06,792 --> 00:13:08,126
[TYPEWRITER KEYS CLACKING]

369
00:13:08,210 --> 00:13:10,087
[TYPEWRITER CARRIAGE RETURNS]

370
00:13:11,338 --> 00:13:12,673
[DOOR CLOSES]

371
00:13:16,259 --> 00:13:18,011
Susie!

372
00:13:18,095 --> 00:13:20,013
-I didn't know you were here.
-I'm not.

373
00:13:20,097 --> 00:13:22,015
I mean, I am, but I don't have to be.

374
00:13:22,099 --> 00:13:23,725
-And you seem busy.
-ANGIE: What, for you?

375
00:13:23,809 --> 00:13:25,810
Never. Come on, get in here, you.

376
00:13:25,894 --> 00:13:27,729
Come on.

377
00:13:28,772 --> 00:13:30,773
Take a load off. Have a seat.

378
00:13:30,857 --> 00:13:33,109
-Here?
-Sure.

379
00:13:33,193 --> 00:13:34,277
Thank God.

380
00:13:34,361 --> 00:13:37,572
So, your girl.

381
00:13:37,656 --> 00:13:39,365
-What about her?
-She's been on fire.

382
00:13:39,449 --> 00:13:41,951
I haven't missed a show.
Last night, I came to see her.

383
00:13:42,035 --> 00:13:44,329
[CHUCKLES]: Left before Shy.
Don't tell Shy.

384
00:13:44,413 --> 00:13:46,914
Snitch? No, I wouldn't do that.
You can trust me.

385
00:13:46,998 --> 00:13:48,541
The way she makes changes to that act

386
00:13:48,625 --> 00:13:50,293
-from night to night…
-She'll stop doing that.

387
00:13:50,377 --> 00:13:52,128
No, it's so skillful. I love it.

388
00:13:52,212 --> 00:13:53,796
Then she'll keep doing it.
I'll make her do it if she won't.

389
00:13:53,880 --> 00:13:55,048
So, what can I do for you?

390
00:13:55,132 --> 00:13:57,050
Nothing. Everything's good.

391
00:13:57,134 --> 00:13:58,593
SECRETARY: There's
a problem with her check!

392
00:13:58,677 --> 00:14:00,845
No, there's not. No, there's not!

393
00:14:00,929 --> 00:14:02,889
She told me there's a problem!

394
00:14:02,973 --> 00:14:04,140
There's no problem!

395
00:14:04,224 --> 00:14:06,017
I think the arthritis is
affecting her memory.

396
00:14:06,101 --> 00:14:07,810
Is that the check?
Let me see it. Is it short?

397
00:14:07,894 --> 00:14:10,480
No. In fact, it might be over.
I… I might owe <i>you</i> money.

398
00:14:10,564 --> 00:14:11,689
Let me see that.

399
00:14:11,773 --> 00:14:13,733
We've had some
bookkeeping problems lately,

400
00:14:13,817 --> 00:14:15,610
checks coming up short.

401
00:14:15,694 --> 00:14:17,195
I think this is short.

402
00:14:17,279 --> 00:14:18,571
-Margaret!
-Yeah?!

403
00:14:18,655 --> 00:14:20,740
Tell one of the guys to
bring the head of payroll here!

404
00:14:20,824 --> 00:14:22,784
-No, it's okay!
-Bring him here! I want to show him!

405
00:14:22,868 --> 00:14:26,329
Oh, you meant bring
all of him, not just his…

406
00:14:26,413 --> 00:14:28,539
I mean, I misunderstood.

407
00:14:28,623 --> 00:14:29,749
You know what? This is an easy fix.

408
00:14:29,833 --> 00:14:31,167
You can stay until he gets here.

409
00:14:31,251 --> 00:14:32,752
I've got a plane to catch.

410
00:14:32,836 --> 00:14:34,295
But you go ahead and keep that

411
00:14:34,379 --> 00:14:35,755
and do whatever you want with it,

412
00:14:35,839 --> 00:14:37,965
and I will see you later, Angie.

413
00:14:38,049 --> 00:14:39,551
Okay. No problem. Hey!

414
00:14:39,635 --> 00:14:41,512
She's on fire, your girl.

415
00:14:41,596 --> 00:14:44,181
Yuppers. I'll keep stoking those flames.

416
00:14:44,265 --> 00:14:46,183
[CHUCKLES] Okay.
Thank you so much, Ange.

417
00:14:46,267 --> 00:14:47,560
No problem. Any time.

418
00:14:50,438 --> 00:14:51,939
Who taught you how to work with plaster?

419
00:14:52,023 --> 00:14:53,190
ARCHIE: My Aunt Mabel.

420
00:14:53,274 --> 00:14:55,150
Never married, grip like a vice.

421
00:14:55,234 --> 00:14:56,652
These are her coveralls.

422
00:14:56,736 --> 00:14:58,529
You both shared that trim figure.

423
00:14:58,613 --> 00:15:00,614
I should have all this
done by tomorrow night.

424
00:15:00,698 --> 00:15:03,117
Then we can start sanding and smoothing.

425
00:15:03,201 --> 00:15:05,994
No. Arch, take a night
off every once in a while.

426
00:15:06,078 --> 00:15:07,496
Imogene must be having a fit.

427
00:15:07,580 --> 00:15:09,790
Hey. Who's the king of the castle?

428
00:15:09,874 --> 00:15:11,291
Who's the top dog in the pack?

429
00:15:11,375 --> 00:15:13,001
Who's the <i>capo di tutti capi?</i>

430
00:15:13,085 --> 00:15:14,044
-Imogene.
-Yeah.

431
00:15:14,128 --> 00:15:16,255
But you're a close second.

432
00:15:16,339 --> 00:15:17,548
Damn.

433
00:15:17,632 --> 00:15:19,383
ARCHIE: Fuse again?

434
00:15:19,467 --> 00:15:20,759
JOEL: Be right back.

435
00:15:20,843 --> 00:15:22,970
[SIGHS]

436
00:15:23,054 --> 00:15:25,056
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

437
00:15:29,685 --> 00:15:31,019
[CHATTER STOPS]

438
00:15:31,103 --> 00:15:32,604
Hey, guys. Just me.

439
00:15:32,688 --> 00:15:34,398
[CHATTER RESUMES]

440
00:15:35,441 --> 00:15:37,067
Now, remember,

441
00:15:37,151 --> 00:15:39,069
every time you guys plug
in that electric percolator,

442
00:15:39,153 --> 00:15:40,904
I'm sanding in the dark.

443
00:15:40,988 --> 00:15:42,281
Thanks, Jiao-long.

444
00:15:42,365 --> 00:15:44,367
We'll figure this out eventually.

445
00:15:53,960 --> 00:15:55,878
Hi.

446
00:15:55,962 --> 00:15:58,922
-Hi.
-Says she knows you?

447
00:15:59,006 --> 00:16:01,258
You guys should officially meet.

448
00:16:01,342 --> 00:16:02,384
Arch, this is Mei.

449
00:16:02,468 --> 00:16:06,430
Mei's the building's, uh… person girl.

450
00:16:06,514 --> 00:16:08,140
ARCHIE: I see.

451
00:16:08,224 --> 00:16:10,768
I'm Archie, Joel's friend boy.

452
00:16:10,852 --> 00:16:12,603
Nice to officially meet you.

453
00:16:12,687 --> 00:16:14,688
I brought you something.

454
00:16:14,772 --> 00:16:15,898
[SPEAKING CHINESE]

455
00:16:15,982 --> 00:16:18,484
-What's this?
-MEI: Patience.

456
00:16:18,568 --> 00:16:20,027
-It's a surprise.
-JOEL: You usually don't wait

457
00:16:20,111 --> 00:16:21,320
for a surprise.

458
00:16:21,404 --> 00:16:23,954
-That's why it's a surprise.
-[MEI SPEAKING CHINESE]

459
00:16:27,410 --> 00:16:29,328
Oh, a jukebox.

460
00:16:29,412 --> 00:16:30,913
A jukebox.

461
00:16:30,997 --> 00:16:32,748
-It's fantastic.
-It's a beaut.

462
00:16:32,832 --> 00:16:34,291
How much is it gonna set me back?

463
00:16:34,375 --> 00:16:35,626
It's free.

464
00:16:35,710 --> 00:16:37,377
My uncle had it in his bowling alley,

465
00:16:37,461 --> 00:16:38,879
and he sold the alley.

466
00:16:38,963 --> 00:16:40,130
-Good deal.
-And it works?

467
00:16:40,214 --> 00:16:42,425
-Just listen.
-[COIN JINGLES]

468
00:16:43,676 --> 00:16:46,304
This is one of my favorites.

469
00:16:47,930 --> 00:16:49,932
[POP SONG PLAYING]

470
00:16:51,392 --> 00:16:52,726
[WOMAN SINGING CHINESE]

471
00:16:52,810 --> 00:16:54,603
This isn't English.

472
00:16:54,687 --> 00:16:57,941
-Archie's kind of an amateur linguist.
-[MEI LAUGHS]

473
00:16:58,025 --> 00:16:59,359
They're all Chinese.

474
00:16:59,443 --> 00:17:01,236
Well, surprisingly, my uncle's Chinese.

475
00:17:01,320 --> 00:17:03,322
I kind of like it.

476
00:17:08,702 --> 00:17:10,620
It grows on you.

477
00:17:10,704 --> 00:17:12,331
See?

478
00:17:14,333 --> 00:17:15,792
So, what's the song about?

479
00:17:15,876 --> 00:17:17,794
Oh, it's the usual stuff.

480
00:17:17,878 --> 00:17:21,130
Boy meets girl, boy loses girl,

481
00:17:21,214 --> 00:17:24,092
girl buys knife with 12-inch blade,

482
00:17:24,176 --> 00:17:28,555
boy loses thumb, boy loses hand.

483
00:17:28,639 --> 00:17:31,642
I like Rosemary Clooney's version better.

484
00:17:33,435 --> 00:17:35,437
♪♪

485
00:17:50,619 --> 00:17:53,372
You're right. It's growing on me.

486
00:17:56,959 --> 00:17:58,293
Thanks for dropping by.

487
00:17:58,377 --> 00:17:59,627
Thanks for the dip.

488
00:17:59,711 --> 00:18:02,630
-And thank your uncle for me.
-Who?

489
00:18:02,714 --> 00:18:04,048
Nice to meet you, Archie.

490
00:18:04,132 --> 00:18:06,134
ARCHIE: Likewise.

491
00:18:11,765 --> 00:18:14,309
-What?
-Nothing. Just…

492
00:18:14,393 --> 00:18:16,311
Nice person girl.

